item.title: Brain pounding eyes vibrating too much computer
item.description: Last night when I finally went to sleep around 11 pm my brain was pounding headachey and my eyes were vibrating in a strange way like, not in a good way. I chalk it up to too much time spent on my computer. it kept me awake for a while, but I was finally able to calm myself down into sleep. I’m on my way to the dentist now, recording this with voice transcription.

item.title: soon thereafter, at Majingos...
item.description: ##00:54 Friday 28 November 2014 JST## On my way out of Roppongi, I shook the hands of the various bar managers/owners who said hello, and I took a liking to Ken, who had white hairs in his beard. He invited me to come up just to see the place so I could come back next time. Okay; that can’t hurt, I figured, and followed him up to 6th floor of some building.

item.title: eyes
item.description: Eye Exam 3:58pm CST Wednesday 1 March 2000 KTRU was fun today, but not stellar or even spectacular music-wise. I did play two pretty cool songs - one jungle and one almost blues tune. My mom called during my radio show to congratulate me and Wende! She saw my marriage news in The Feel Good Net. I put on a long song and we talked for about 10 minutes while it played.
